# Railway Deployment — Quick Setup

## 1. Deploy to Railway
Push this entire folder to a GitHub repo, then connect it to Railway.

## 2. Add Environment Variables in Railway Dashboard
Go to: Your Service → Variables → Add all these:

```
PORT=4000
NODE_ENV=production
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-J2IqLslp...
HUBSPOT_ACCESS_TOKEN=pat-eu1-b07d...
APOLLO_API_KEY=U_G8KEWJ...
CLAY_API_KEY=574c439f...
SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=xoxe-1-My0x...
ICP_INDUSTRIES=marketing agencies,saas,ecommerce
ICP_LOCATIONS=morocco,france,canada,usa
ICP_MIN_EMPLOYEES=5
ICP_MAX_EMPLOYEES=100
```

## 3. After first deploy
Copy your Railway public URL (e.g. https://xxx.up.railway.app)
Then update frontend/.env:
  REACT_APP_API_URL=https://xxx.up.railway.app/api

## 4. Health check
Visit: https://xxx.up.railway.app/health
Expected response: {"status":"ok","timestamp":"..."}
